itemListElement.name: Downtown Seattle Self-Guided Walking Audio Tour

name: Downtown Seattle Self-Guided Walking Audio Tour
description:
Experience breathtaking scenery, history, and eccentric culture with this self-guided walking tour of Seattle. Hear about aquatic life and view the majestic Seattle Aquarium. Learn about the Coast Salish and how the city rose from a homestead! See breathtaking skyscrapers and stroll past Pioneer Square, the heart of Seattle. You'll also learn how the city became a hub for coffee and grunge and walk past the bustling Pike Place Market! As a bonus, this package also includes a tour through Space Needle!

After booking, check your email to download the separate Audio Tour Guide App by Action, enter your unique password, and access your tour. These steps require good internet/Wi-Fi access. From there, follow the audio instructions and the route.

Buy once, use for one year! Ideal for extended visits and return trips over the next 12 months.

This isn't an entrance ticket. Check opening hours before your visit.

review.name: Great Tour To Do At Your Own Pace!
review.reviewBody: I chose to do this tour on my first day in Seattle as it was going to be a rainy day, and I wanted opportunities to stop and dry off, and learn at my own pace, and the app worked well! Once I purchased the tour, I was given clear and easy instructions to follow on how to download the app. I was happy to learn that once downloaded, it could be used offline. The app worked great and was able to follow my movements and provide interesting facts with each location I was walking past. Im glad I did this type of tour and will be looking to do this in other cities.

review.name: Good value for the experience
review.reviewBody: Very good information and easy to follow.  The maps that are included make it easy to get back on the route if a detour is desired.  Even gives directions to the starting point using Google maps.

review.name: great Tour if you like to go at your own pace
review.reviewBody: My partner and I did Both seattle tours, it was a great way to see all the highlights. we loved that you can Go at your own pace, pause to sped time at different places, and there are options for "more information" so you can listen to aditional stories about some of the stops. we both agreed we would like to do this type of tour in every city we visit!

review.name: Very Informative
review.reviewBody: Great, super informative tour that kept me entertained. Also did the Space Needle tour which was very informative. It was worth taking this tour.

itemListElement.name: 3 Hour Private Tour in Seattle Seaside Serenity

name: 3 Hour Private Tour in Seattle Seaside Serenity
description: Discover Seattle in a way that sets our tour apart from the rest. Delight in a genuine local experience as you savor the city's best-kept secret  authentic fish and chips at a cherished local hotspot. Immerse yourself in the remarkable engineering marvel of the Ballard Locks fish ladders, an exclusive behind-the-scenes insight into the region's maritime heritage. Trek the scenic Discovery Park lighthouse trail, where nature's tranquility meets urban sophistication. And as the grand finale, be swept away by the breathtaking panoramic views of Seattle's skyline and the majestic Mount Rainier from Kerry Park. This isn't just a tour; it's an unparalleled journey that intertwines local flavors, history, and natural beauty, offering a unique perspective that only Seattle can provide.

itemListElement.name: Elevated Mount Rainier Day Private Tour in Oregon

name: Elevated Mount Rainier Day Private Tour in Oregon
description:
Many people travel to Mt. Rainier every year - about 2.5 million to be exact. But few will have the opportunity to do so with the attention to detail, depth of knowledge, and the luxurious touch of a First Nature Tours experience. 

Our team of professional guides, who have spent years trekking on Mt. Rainier, will provide insider knowledge and personalized attention each step of the way. We pride ourselves in elevating these experiences above and beyond what you find elsewhere.

name: Wine, Bread, Cheese and Chocolate
description:
What else is there to say?!

This local walking tour features 8 of Downtown Seattles best wine shops, cheese mongers, bakeries, restaurants, and chocolatiers. 

You can expect tastings of 6 different artisan wines, along with food pairings designed to express the best of the Pacific Northwest.

In addition to these pairings, the tour makes stops at 3 producers and vendors in Pike Place Market to taste cheese, bread and the glorious combination of the two. 

We know you wont want to wait until the end for dessert, so we mix in chocolate throughout the tour. Expect some unbelievably good truffles, bars and drinking chocolates from across the globe. 

As you eat and drink your way through local culture, your knowledgeable guide will share stories and insights from their personal experience as a lover of Northwest food.

By the end we hope you can express your own views as to what makes the Seattle food scene so special. 

Come eat with us!

Must be 21+ to participate

review.name: Great experience!
review.reviewBody: Will was very knowledgeable and took us to places we may have missed on our own. Got to taste wine, cheese, pasta, chocolate and sampled some gourmet condiments. Highly recommend!

review.name: Do it!!
review.reviewBody: I honestly would recommend this to anyone I know. Really great snacks, drinks and chocolate. Fun is definitely an understatement!!

review.name: Amazing tour guide!
review.reviewBody: Jade was amazingly nice and captured our interests from the beginning and tried to meet our expectations based on that!

review.name: Great afternoon!
review.reviewBody: Jade was a great tour guide. We thoroughly enjoyed the tour and the selections. Jade shared lots of information about the area and the taste offerings. Thank you Jade for a great start to our girls trip!

review.name: Great Seattle Food Tour
review.reviewBody: Great food tour. Will was fantastic and I would recommend to my friends and family. One of the best food tours that I have been on.

review.name: BEST wine and food tour ever!!!
review.reviewBody: I took my mother on this for her birthday. This was an amazing tour! It was a great way to get introduced to Seattle's food culture and the Pike Place market. I had so much fun!! Our tour guide was amazing. He taught us so much about different foods, cheeses, and chocolates. We had an amazing time.

review.name: Great outing!
review.reviewBody:
Will was amazing! The value was amazing!  We enjoyed all the food and wine we tried. 
Will was very informative about the town.   We enjoyed everything and would highly recommend to others!

review.name: Fun tour!
review.reviewBody: Ivy was a great guide. She shared her knowledge of the city and Washington as a whole. We had a great time!  We made 5 stops throughout the downtown area, each completely different from the last.

review.name: Highly recommend!
review.reviewBody: We had a wonderful time! We got to experience spots we otherwise would have never gone. Will was a great tour guide, was personable and friendly. Highly recommend!

review.name: Amazing Market Tour
review.reviewBody: This tour was delightful as were the store owners we met along the way. Will was incredibly knowledgeable about the various foods and wines, as well as history of the market and other bits of Seattle trivia. Of the many stops we made, there was only ONE I had been to before, which is saying a lot for someone born and raised in Seattle. I would 100% do this tour again.

itemListElement.name: The Best of Seattle and Majestic Snoqualmie Waterfalls

name: The Best of Seattle and Majestic Snoqualmie Waterfalls
description: Discover The Best of Seattle and Majestic Snoqualmie Waterfalls in one day with our amazing tour package that takes you to the citys top attractions and the breathtaking Snoqualmie Waterfalls! where nature and urban life coexist in harmony. The best and well-known attractions of Seattle City Tour with Snoqualmie Waterfalls has it all. Dont miss this chance to see the best of Seattle on this 7-hour sightseeing tour. Book your tour today and get ready for an unforgettable adventure!

review.name: Great Seattle Tour
review.reviewBody: Mehrdad was our tour guide and made it such a fun and unique experience! The hike down to the lowest viewpoint for Snoqualmie Falls was a great trail and our favorite part.

review.name: Majestic Elegance is the best!
review.reviewBody: We have visited Majestic resorts five times so far and Majestic Elegance is our favorite! One of the reasons we keep coming back again and again are the people that make it special! I would like to mention our butlers Erickson Polanco and Victor, Ismael Castillo at the Elegance Club pool bar, and Rosalia and Sofia Rosaiva at the lobby bar. Please ask for them! They will really make your experience one to remember year after year! We love you guys! Michael and Barbie.

review.name: Seattle and falls tour
review.reviewBody: Daniel was our guide. He was super informative and made it a very nice tour. It was a full day of fun and really cool stops! 100% recommend.

review.name: Great sights
review.reviewBody: Our tour guide and driver, Slav, was amazing. He helped us in and out of the van with great care. He is knowledgeable and a great driver. The views from the various tour stops are beautiful. There is a fair bit of walking. I wouldn't recommend it unless you can walk more than half a mile without getting short of breath.

review.name: Afternoon in Seattle
review.reviewBody: Vladimir was terrific.  He took us to parks which were much more interesting than shopping malls. Enjoyed the waterfalls and the hydro electric powerplant.

review.name: Great day in Seattle
review.reviewBody: Daniel was very informative and showed us so many of the highlights of Seattle. We received water and snacks when we first got on the bus. This tour took us all over the city and the views were amazing!!  I would definitely recommend this to anyone visiting Seattle!

review.name: Really good tour
review.reviewBody: Our Tour Guide, Daniel, did an outstanding job, and dropped us off at the end of the day right back at our condo.  We had a fantastic time.  Worth every penny.

review.name: A great introduction to the Seattle area!
review.reviewBody: Our tour guide - Vlad was absolutely wonderful..be sure to request him!  Tour van was very comfortable, holds 10 +/- but there was only 6 of us.  The tour lasts about 7 hours so you get to see more than just the city...water falls, winery, famous chocolate factory, locks, fish ladder, lakes, and more.  BOOK IT!!

review.name: Enjoyable Tour
review.reviewBody: We really enjoyed the tour (family of 4 with a 6 year old and a 14 year old). We learned so much about Seattle and saw some really cool things. Our tour guide was informative and made sure we saw as many sites as possible. The only issue was that the tickets said the tour started at 7 am and it really didnt start until 9:30 am. I had booked tickets to see the Space Needle at 3 pm and had to move the time. Luckily I was able to pick a later time so it worked out okay.

review.name: Excellent Tour!
review.reviewBody: We had a fantastic day-long tour with Mr. Mehrdad. He picked us up right from the cruise port and took us around the outskirts of the Seattle area. I had no idea how beautiful the area is outside of Seattle. We had a specific itinerary, but we were never rushed at any of the places we visited. We spent a lot of time at the Snoqualmie Waterfalls, Gas Works Park and Boehm's Chocolates. We got some fabulous pictures with the Fremont Troll and at Kerry Park. At the end of the tour, we were taken directly to the airport. This is the perfect tour to take if you have a long wait between your cruise docking and your evening flight.

name: Seattle Seafood Brunch Tour
description:
Trust the city with SEA in its name to deliver the freshest seafood tour this side of the Pacific!

This brunch-hour walking food tour is designed to provide you with all of the classic seafood of the Pacific Northwest, including Salmon, Dungeness Crab, Oysters, Chowder, and Japanese Cuisine. 

The majority of this tour takes place sitting down in restaurants and includes less than a mile of walking in-between stops. 

We will introduce you to some of our favorite vendors in historic Pike Place Market, allowing you to sample the native flavors of the Pacific Northwest in the heart of its largest city. 

Seattle is not only surrounded by water and vibrant aquatic ecosystems, it is also a world-class distribution hub for seafood caught from up and down the coast. Are you looking for the freshest seafood from Alaskan? Well, Seattle is your answer. 

Everybody is welcome to enjoy with us, so let us know ahead of time about any dietary restrictions or mobility concerns.

Cheers!

review.name: A different type of tour
review.reviewBody:
I absolutely loved this experience  

Since I took the tour on a Monday morning it was just me on the tour with Will, the owner of the tour company. It was extremely fun and engaging. I loved how he customizes his tours based on his customers. 

If you are in Seattle and are looking for a different kind of tour Seattle: Premier Seafood Brunch with Market Visit is definitely your choice. It is definitely worth the extra $.

Check out my IG lawyer.traveler.dreamer as I will post about it soon.

review.name: Amazing
review.reviewBody: Tour guide Will was amazing! He was incredibly knowledgeable about all things food and Seattle. Very personable and accommodating to our group with various food likes. Patient as heck with my 85yo parents and 19yo niece. All had a great time sampling the food. Faves were the tacos and pasta! Thanks, Will, for your expertise!

review.name: Great experience
review.reviewBody: Will is very knowledgeable, accommodating,  and friendly.   The people sit our next table was impressed  and asking about our tour.  We had a good time and nice food!  Thank you!

review.name: Great Post Birthday Experience!
review.reviewBody: Great deal to taste many places in a couple hours! Will was accommodating to our need for scooter/handicap access. He provided a wealth of city history and food knowledge. The conversations and food tasting was the best! We enjoyed it immensely!

review.name: Seattle seafood tour
review.reviewBody: We had the best time on this tour! Jade was very friendly and knowledgeable and she made sure to ask our preferences about things. The food was amazing and we went to restaurants I would definitely go back to. Well done.

review.name: Knowledgeable Guide
review.reviewBody: Had a great time. Woody was very knowledgeable and helpful regarding questions about Seattle. There is so much food on this tour, I almost couldnt eat it all.

review.name: Seattle Seafood Tour with Will
review.reviewBody: Will did an amazing job of selecting several great dining options and has a wealth of information about dining in and around the Seattle area.  Definitely a delightful experience!

review.name: Fantastic tour!
review.reviewBody: Wonderful tour. We had a lovely day in Seattle. Jade was a great guide and all the food stops were fabulous. Will definitely be returning for another tour with this company.

review.name: Seafood Tour in Pikes Public Market
review.reviewBody: Delicious seafood brunch tour in comfortable sit down settings in Pikes Public Market. Will was a fantastic host and gave recommendations for all types of food. Great way to taste the seafood of the Pacific Northwest!

review.name: A MUST DO food tour!
review.reviewBody: I highly recommend this tour! Will had a plethora of information and has a very good relationship with many of the vendors. The markets and restaurants he took me to offered the best of what there is. I appreciated his knowledge and laid back and friendly approach!

name: ZZ Inactive 8
description:
Embark on a walking tour around Seattles Space Needle Park, a lush green space full of vibrant art, culture, and enchanting views. Learn the story behind the iconic Space Needle as you walk around the park. Plus, check out totally unique sculptures and creations, from giant glass flowers to a huge sunken fountain! This beautiful park has a lot to see for for the whole family. 

After booking, check your email to download the separate Audio Tour Guide App by Action, enter your unique password, and access your tour. These steps require good internet/Wi-Fi access. From there, follow the audio instructions and the route.

New, extra validity  now yours for an entire year! Use multiple times over multiple trips!

This isn't an entrance ticket. Check opening hours before your visit.

address.streetAddress: 4106 Stone Way N Located in Broadstone Vin

name: Viking Beer Crawl
description:
Why do salmon swim upriver? Do bridge trolls make good security guards? Does that scruffy man drinking a craft beer work on the shipyard, or in tech?

Welcome to life in Seattle. For 3.5 epic hours, we pack in the greatest joys of the Northwest on foot!

This tour pays visit to 2 breweries (under 21 allowed), 2 restaurants and 1 cafe inside the National Nordic Museum, all within walking distance from natural wonders, engineering marvels and a city's proud history. 

Food and Drink are included.

Watch Salmon swim upriver to their ancestral spawning grounds with your own eyes!

Raise the bridges (and the boats!) as they have for over 100 years.

Cheers (Skal!) your new friends and eat fish off a stick like the Viking you always knew you were. 

Ballard is a short distance from downtown, accessible in 25 min by bus, <15 min by car, or 30 min by scooter/bike share. 

The tour includes a total of 2.75 miles of walking on mostly flat ground, but there is plenty of time in-between for rest.

review.name: Fun and interesting walking tour.
review.reviewBody: My husband I were the only people on the beer crawl!  I appreciate that they did not cancel since no one else signed up! We had a great time with Will! He certainly knows and loves his city and he is a wealth of information about Seattle. We learned about Seattles history and visited some great breweries and restaurants. The fried chicken at Cookies Fried Chicken was amazing and my husband got to try Rainier beer while which is something he had been wanting to do for a long time. I would highly recommend this tour; it was a lot of fun.

review.name: Beer-walking in Ballard
review.reviewBody:
Such a wonderful walking tour! Our fantastic and knowledgeable guide Will, took us to three bars: Bizarre Brewing,  Skl, and Fair Isle Brewingall featuring their refreshing own spin on what it means to be a brew house in this Scandinavian town. Snackslike Seasonal Skewers at Sklwere included at each stop. (Although not Viking, a bucket of fried chicken at Cookies Country Kitchen was too irresistible for our group to pass up.) 
Along the way, Will brought us up to speed on a bit of Ballards history, taking us to see the salmon fish ladders at the Ballard Locks, and walking through its lovely park and gardens. We even made a quick stop in front of the National Nordic Museum to see its towering troll guard, Frankie Feetsplinters, created by Danish artist Thomas Dambo. 
If youre up for a some local brew and bitesand historywhile taking a stroll through Seattles own Scandinavian streets, this is the tour for you.

review.name: Loved seeing the Sea Lions
review.reviewBody: We had a great time. Will was knowledgeable and he took us to interesting places. Food and drinks terrific. We took a very nice tour of Ballard and also saw wildlife.

review.name: Fascinating Ballard adventure!
review.reviewBody:
Oh wow! Our guide,Laura, was just wonderful, and it was immediately obvious that this tour company in particular is very  client-minded, well-informed..and ended up being such an excellent value for us as we had an exceptional tour. 
We learned a lot about the Ballard area of Seattle, got some fantastic photos of amazing sights and experiences, and had delicious bites & sips along the way. It turned out that it was just the two of us and Laura on the tour,  but she treated us like good friends she was so kind as to immediately flex the tour to better accommodate us, the weather, and a few things we confessed wed really like to see/experience!  Altogether highly recommend for a memorable and delightful experience!

review.name: Like Brewery Hopping with a Friend
review.reviewBody: Our tour with Will was like going brewery hopping with a friend!  We visited some great spots and had his guidance on specific beers to try.  The staff knew him and each place had that welcome brew-scene culture.  He hooked it up with some great food, as well.  At the start, he asked us what we wanted our afternoon to include, so in addition to some brewery spots, he prioritized taking us to the Ballard Locks.  Will had stories to tell about the history and function of the Locks, and it really just felt like visiting a friend and them sharing about their city.  At the end, he shared some additional recommendations (and what to skip!) around Ballad and Seattle Downtown.  Great spots, personalized wanderings, and easy conversation.  Thanks, Will!

review.name: A Stroll Around Seattle
review.reviewBody: Our guide took us to several brewpubs in the warehouse district. We were able to sample about 20 different beers, plus we had a variiety of foods that were unique to each locale. Really fun to hang out and talk while doing a beer crawl on a perfect Seattle afternoon!

review.name: Brewery and restaurant tour
review.reviewBody: Simply a great tour. Will is very knowledgeable but nothing felt scripted. It was like we were spending time with a friend who knows a lot about Seattle. Would do it again in a heartbeat

itemListElement.name: 7-Hour Electric Bike City Tour Featuring Food, Parks and a Museum

name: 7-Hour Electric Bike City Tour Featuring Food, Parks and a Museum
description:
Embark on an extraordinary 7-hour E-bike adventure through Seattle, an immersive journey of flavors, stories, and vistas. Don't let the duration deter you  every moment is designed for comfort and wonder.

Food, bike rentals and museum admittance are included, so sit back and let the city ride through you:

Glide through the Japanese Gardens

Catch sight of iconic floating houseboats

Let the MOHAI bring history alive

Watch the Olympic Sculpture Park merge art and nature

Listen as the Lighthouse offers maritime tales

Move with nature at the Ballard Locks

Ask the Troll for passage under his bridge

And gaze at The Emerald City from all its angles

Did I mention therell be food? Start the Journey off with a beverage and treats from a popular local bakery. Snacks will be offered along the way. And lunch will be well earned!

Uncover Seattle's heart, and embrace a day that enriches your soul.

The route is 25 miles. The Bikes are electric. Please reach out about any concerns.

itemListElement.name: Insider's Breakfast and Culture Tour of Pike Place Market

name: Insider's Breakfast and Culture Tour of Pike Place Market
description:
VOTED 10 BEST FOOD TOURS IN THE COUNTRY BY USA TODAY!

Get ahead of peak crowds and join us for this special offering as we take you behind the scenes on an early-morning exploration of Pike Place Market. Our guides on this tour are deeply rooted members of the community who will truly take you to Meet The Producer using their years of experience in the neighborhood. Feel like a local as you walk and eat your way through the best morning bites we can offer! Learn the names and stories of the people who operate the businesses, as our guides give you the full history of how Pike Place became The Soul of Seattle.

Savor Seattle is permitted and licensed by the Pike Place Market Preservation and Development Authority (PDA) to operate tours in the Pike Place Market Historical District. The PDA requires any business or person conducting paid tours within its properties and in the public areas of the historical district to be pre-approved and to have a license for this activity.

review.name: Fantastic tour
review.reviewBody: Kacey was amazing. Super knowledgeable and fun - everyone knew her at the market! Highly recommend. Great food and interesting facts.

review.name: So fun!!!
review.reviewBody: Kacey was an amazing guide. Ton of personality, great stories, amazing food and drinks. Probably most favorite food tour in a long time. I also loved learning about the community and all the support for small businesses, giving back to the people. This was a real treat. Thank you!

review.name: Best guide and tour
review.reviewBody: Casey our tour guide was amazing and so friendly. Shes so knowledgeable about the Pike Place Market. We thoroughly enjoyed our tour and all the places on our stop.

review.name: The food delicious, the staff of Pike Place were all engaging and friendly. I loved the sense of community.
review.reviewBody: The food was amazing, Kasey was amazing, and I had so much fun. On my next visit to Seattle, if I should do another excursion, I hope Kasey is the tour guide. The tour was rich with history and nothing will compare to unmistakable Gum Wall.

review.name: Pike Place Market tour with Kasey.
review.reviewBody: Pike Place Market is an amazing place to wonder about but we highly recommend going on the tour.   The food samples were fantastic but the backstories provided by our guide Kasey were the best part of the day.   Kasey shared so much history about how Pike Place Market came to be as well as stories about many of the owners and employees you will see in the Market.  Six (6) stars for Kasey and the tour!

review.name: Awesome tour with Casey!
review.reviewBody: Our tour guide, Casey, was so amazing! She was so nice and helpful and knew so much about the area. Our tour was amazing with her!

review.name: Fabulous Tour
review.reviewBody: We highly recommend this tour. Heather, our guide, was extremely knowledgeable about the Pike Place Market. We enjoyed lots of fantastic food and learned lots of fun facts about the market.

review.name: Worthwhile
review.reviewBody: Great vendors and a great host.  The food was good but so was the history.  I felt I got to know the area.  Ive already recommended to others!

review.name: Yummy
review.reviewBody: Excellent tour.  Exceptional guide in the tour that provided both history and current information on the market. A wide variety of cuisines and large enough samples to get a good ideas of each vendors specialties.

review.name: Great tour, great food, great guide.
review.reviewBody: Our guide Judson was fantastic.  His love for the market and it's culture radiated from him.  He was so knowledgeable about the history of the market and the foods served there, but he was also open to learning new things like that in France the dauphinoise (which we had at La Panier and was amazing) is a side dish, not a savory pastry.  The tastings were great, well curated, and plenty to keep you from feeling hungry.  I only wish there were more opportunities to sit during the tour.  I would definitely recommend this tour to anyone!

address.streetAddress: 1410 18th Ave 4th Floor of the Washington Convention Center

itemListElement.name: Self-Guided Scavenger Hunt: Seattle By The Sound

name: Self-Guided Scavenger Hunt: Seattle By The Sound
description:
Lets Roam is the #1 app-led adventure hunt company. Explore the best landmarks and hidden gems, answering trivia questions and taking on thrilling challenges. Team up with friends or compete against them as you uncover new facts and create unforgettable memories. 

Lets Roam Adventure Hunts are perfect for any occasionwhether it's a casual outing, a bachelorette party, a birthday celebration, or a corporate team-building event! 

Each player chooses an interactive role, with challenges tailored just for them.

review.name: Scavenger hunt
review.reviewBody: It was great for my daughter, and a lot of fun!!! Not too hard to walk and a lot of great info. Not sure what else you could ask for in a scavenger hunt, we look forward to doing more of them!
